
Overview of noun bomb

The noun bomb has 3 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (8) bomb -- (an explosive device fused to explode under specific conditions)
2. (1) bomb calorimeter, bomb -- (strong sealed vessel for measuring heat of combustion)
3. turkey, bomb, dud -- (an event that fails badly or is totally ineffectual; "the first experiment was a real turkey"; "the meeting was a dud as far as new business was concerned")

Overview of verb bomb

The verb bomb has 2 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (3) bombard, bomb -- (throw bombs at or attack with bombs; "The Americans bombed Dresden")
2. fail, flunk, bomb, flush it -- (fail to get a passing grade; "She studied hard but failed nevertheless"; "Did I fail the test?")
